1
00:00:24,991 --> 00:00:27,494
[ Door Buzzer Buzzing ]
DADDY.

2
00:00:30,497 --> 00:00:32,499
DADDY, ARE YOU HOME ?
MAYBE HE ISN'T.

3
00:00:32,999 --> 00:00:35,001
OF COURSE HE IS.
DADDY !

4
00:00:35,001 --> 00:00:38,004
[ Knocking ]
FIND HIM ?

5
00:00:38,004 --> 00:00:42,609
DOES IT LOOK LIKE
I FOUND HIM, STANLEY ?
WELL, I JUST THOUGHT--

6
00:00:47,514 --> 00:00:49,582
DAD !

7
00:00:50,784 --> 00:00:53,186
DADDY.

8
00:00:53,586 --> 00:00:57,991
DON'T WORRY ABOUT
YOUR FATHER, BARBARA.
I'M SURE HE'S ALL RIGHT.

9
00:00:57,991 --> 00:00:59,993
OH, I DON'T KNOW.

10
00:01:01,911 --> 00:01:05,348
[ Stanley ]
HONEY, I'M SURE--
DADDY !

11
00:01:06,549 --> 00:01:08,952
DADDY, ARE YOU THERE ?

12
00:01:08,952 --> 00:01:11,354
[ Sighs ]
WE SHOULDN'T HAVE
LEFT HIM ALONE.

13
00:01:11,755 --> 00:01:15,458
HE WANTED TO COME HERE.
DON'T GET YOURSELF ALL UPSET.
DADDY !

14
00:01:15,458 --> 00:01:18,261
HONEY.  WHAT--
STANLEY !

15
00:01:18,261 --> 00:01:20,663
OKAY, I'M COMING.
I'M COMING !
DADDY !

16
00:01:22,665 --> 00:01:25,518
I TOLD YOU
HE SHOULD NOT
BE LEFT ALONE.

17
00:01:25,935 --> 00:01:29,355
IT'S TOO BIG
FOR ONE MAN.
HE WANTED TO BE LEFT ALONE.

18
00:01:29,355 --> 00:01:32,358
BULL !  YOU ALWAYS
TAKE HIS SIDE.
DADDY !  DAD !

19
00:01:41,701 --> 00:01:43,703
[ Margin Bell Dings ]

20
00:01:49,209 --> 00:01:51,795
[ Margin Bell Dings ]

21
00:01:59,752 --> 00:02:01,754
[ Margin Bell Dings ]

22
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:10,263
[ Margin Bell Dings ]

23
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:19,789
[ Engine Roaring ]

24
00:02:19,789 --> 00:02:23,793
[ Men Speaking German ]

25
00:02:56,893 --> 00:03:01,898
???? [ Classical ]

26
00:05:08,992 --> 00:05:13,997
???? [ Continues ]

27
00:05:32,515 --> 00:05:35,268
AAAH !

28
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:43,860
[ Margin Bell Dings ]

29
00:05:52,885 --> 00:05:55,288
???? [ Classical ]

30
00:06:02,862 --> 00:06:04,964
???? [ Stops ]

31
00:06:16,909 --> 00:06:18,961
[ Margin Bell Dings ]

32
00:06:19,412 --> 00:06:21,397
WHO ARE YOU ?
YOUR OUTFIT ?
WHERE YOU GOING ?

33
00:06:21,397 --> 00:06:23,900
I DON'T KNOW.
YOU DON'T KNOW ?
HOW COME ?

34
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:26,903
I JUST MOVED UP.
LET ME SEE
YOUR DOG TAGS.

35
00:06:26,903 --> 00:06:28,905
WHERE ARE THEY ?

36
00:06:28,905 --> 00:06:31,407
I-- I CAN'T FIND THEM.
HE'S A KRAUT !

37
00:06:31,908 --> 00:06:33,409
HE DON'T LOOK LIKE ONE.
I'M NOT !
 I'M AN AMERICAN.

38
00:06:33,910 --> 00:06:35,912
PROVE IT !
PROVE IT ?

39
00:06:35,912 --> 00:06:38,414
WHO PLAYS THIRD
FOR THE TIGERS ?
THE TIGERS ?

40
00:06:38,414 --> 00:06:41,918
THE DETROIT TIGERS.
[ Artillery Exploding ]

41
00:06:41,918 --> 00:06:43,920
WHO IS IT ?
I DON'T KNOW.

42
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,922
WHY ASK HIM ?
IT CAME INTO MY HEAD.

43
00:06:45,922 --> 00:06:48,424
YOU GUYS GO ON WITHOUT ME.
WHERE'S YOUR WEAPON ?

44
00:06:48,424 --> 00:06:50,426
I DON'T HAVE ONE.
EVERYBODY'S GOT ONE !

45
00:06:50,426 --> 00:06:54,430
I'M A CHAPLAIN.
ASSISTANT CHAPLAIN.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME ?

46
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:58,434
PILGRIM.
YOU KNOW WHY THIS GOT
THREE SIDES ON IT ?

47
00:06:58,434 --> 00:07:02,438
MAKES A SLIT
THAT DON'T CLOSE UP.
GEE, THAT'S GREAT.

48
00:07:02,939 --> 00:07:05,441
A G.I. KNIFE
MAKES A SLIT.
RIGHT.

49
00:07:05,942 --> 00:07:07,944
SLIT CLOSES UP,
RIGHT ?
RIGHT.

50
00:07:07,944 --> 00:07:09,946
THIS MAKES
A THREE-SIDED SLIT.

51
00:07:09,946 --> 00:07:12,448
IT KILLS YOU.
[ Artillery Exploding ]

52
00:07:12,448 --> 00:07:14,400
[ Screams ]

53
00:07:14,801 --> 00:07:16,502
WHAT'S THAT ?
CHAPLAIN'S ASSISTANT.

54
00:07:16,502 --> 00:07:19,305
NO SHIT !
WHAT'S YOUR NAME ?
HIS NAME'S PILGRIM.

55
00:07:19,305 --> 00:07:21,707
YOU KNOW HOW TO PRAY ?
START PRAYING !

56
00:07:23,409 --> 00:07:26,479
WHERE ARE WE,
CORP ?
BELGIUM, STUPID.

57
00:07:26,479 --> 00:07:30,216
YOU TELL PAUL LAZZARO
WHERE WE ARE !
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE OF KRAUTS !

58
00:07:30,216 --> 00:07:31,918
YOU GOT US HERE.
GET US OUT !

59
00:07:32,351 --> 00:07:35,338
"OUR FATHER WHO ART IN HEAVEN,
 HALLOWED BE THY NAME.

60
00:07:35,338 --> 00:07:38,841
"THY KINGDOM COME.
 THY WILL BE DONE ON EARTH
 AS IT IS IN HEAVEN.

61
00:07:38,841 --> 00:07:40,843
GIVE US THIS DAY OUR DAILY--"

62
00:07:40,843 --> 00:07:44,347
[ Corporal ]
...JUST BEYOND THOSE TREES
THERE'S A FARMHOUSE.

63
00:07:44,347 --> 00:07:46,849
GO ON WITHOUT ME.
I'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

64
00:07:46,849 --> 00:07:48,734
I'M GONNA
SCOUT THAT FARMHOUSE.

65
00:07:48,734 --> 00:07:52,822
AND IF IT'S CLEAR,
I'LL FIRE MY CARBINE
THREE TIMES SPACED.

66
00:07:52,822 --> 00:07:54,824
GOT IT !

67
00:08:00,830 --> 00:08:04,333
THAT SON OF A BITCH
DITCHES US,
I'LL KILL HIM.

68
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:06,285
WE COULD SURRENDER.
WHAT ?

69
00:08:06,285 --> 00:08:08,788
WE COULD SURRENDER,
COULDN'T WE ?

70
00:08:09,288 --> 00:08:10,790
WE'D JUST
HAVE TO STAY HERE--

71
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:14,794
ME AND THE CORPORAL
AND THE DAGO, WE'RE AMERICANS !
WE DON'T SURRENDER !  GOT THAT ?

72
00:08:14,794 --> 00:08:17,797
HE'S TOOK OFF.

73
00:08:21,801 --> 00:08:23,803
[ Exhales ]

74
00:08:25,805 --> 00:08:28,307
[ Sighs ]

75
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:32,812
THAT CORPORAL.

76
00:08:32,812 --> 00:08:36,315
HE'LL GET BACK HOME
AFTER THE WAR.

77
00:08:36,315 --> 00:08:38,317
HE'LL BE A BIG HERO.

78
00:08:38,818 --> 00:08:41,821
DAMES'LL BE CLIMBIN'
ALL OVER HIM.

79
00:08:41,821 --> 00:08:46,325
COUPLE OF YEARS GO BY,
AND ONE DAY THERE'S
GONNA BE A KNOCK ON HIS DOOR,

80
00:08:46,325 --> 00:08:49,328
AND THERE'LL BE THIS STRANGER.

81
00:08:49,328 --> 00:08:53,833
"PAUL LAZZARO SENT ME,"
THE STRANGER WILL SAY
AND SHOOT HIS PECKER OFF.

82
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:58,337
STRANGER WILL GIVE HIM A COUPLE
OF SECONDS TO THINK ABOUT
WHO PAUL LAZZARO IS...

83
00:08:58,337 --> 00:09:01,340
AND WHAT LIFE'S GONNA BE LIKE
WITHOUT A PECKER,

84
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:04,844
THEN HE'LL SHOOT HIM ONCE
IN THE GUTS AND WALK AWAY.

85
00:09:04,844 --> 00:09:06,846
YES.

86
00:09:06,846 --> 00:09:10,850
[ Woman ]
BILLY, YOU TIME TRIPPING AGAIN ?

87
00:09:11,350 --> 00:09:15,354
I CAN ALWAYS TELL, YOU KNOW,
WHEN YOU'VE BEEN TIME TRIPPING.

88
00:09:18,858 --> 00:09:21,861
YOU WERE BACK IN THE WAR,
WEREN'T YOU ?

89
00:09:23,362 --> 00:09:27,366
TIME TRAVEL'S A BITCH
FOR YOU, ISN'T IT ?
PARTICULARLY THE WAR.

90
00:09:27,366 --> 00:09:30,870
I CAN'T HELP IT.

91
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:35,875
WHY DON'T WE SEE IF
OLD MOTHU MONTANA CAN'T KEEP
YOU STUCK RIGHT HERE FOR AWHILE.

92
00:09:37,376 --> 00:09:41,380
HOW ABOUT
A LITTLE KISS ?
A LITTLE KISS ?

93
00:09:41,380 --> 00:09:42,882
- A LITTLE KI--
- A WHAT ?

94
00:09:43,382 --> 00:09:46,385
- [ Sighs ]
  A LITTLE KISS.
- YOU FUCKIN' FAGGOT !

95
00:09:46,385 --> 00:09:48,888
WHAT'S THE MATTER ?
YOU FUCKIN' FAIRY !

96
00:09:48,888 --> 00:09:52,391
[ Dogs Barking ]
[ Indistinct Shouting ]

97
00:09:52,391 --> 00:09:54,393
WHAT'S THE MATTER, FAGGOT ?

98
00:09:54,393 --> 00:09:56,395
I WAS THINKIN' OF A GIRL.
[ Lazzaro ]
HE WANTED TO KISS ME.

99
00:09:56,896 --> 00:09:58,397
[ Shouting ]
[ Barking Continues ]

100
00:09:58,397 --> 00:10:00,900
I WAS IMAGINING THINGS
AND I WAS--

101
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:04,220
[ Barking ]
[ Arguing Continues ]

102
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:06,656
KRAUTS !

103
00:10:10,009 --> 00:10:13,462
STEHEN SIE AUF.

104
00:10:19,468 --> 00:10:22,471
[ Man, Woman Moaning ]

105
00:10:26,475 --> 00:10:29,478
[ Woman ]
BILLY, YOU'RE WONDERFUL.

106
00:10:31,981 --> 00:10:33,983
[ Kissing ]

107
00:10:33,983 --> 00:10:37,486
[ Woman ]
I'M SO GLAD I WAITED.

108
00:10:37,486 --> 00:10:40,489
[ Billy ]
I'M GLAD
WE WAITED TOO.

109
00:10:40,489 --> 00:10:45,494
OTHERWISE, IT WOULDN'T OF SEEMED
THE SAME TONIGHT.
NO, IT WOULDN'T.

110
00:10:45,494 --> 00:10:49,999
[ Woman ]
IT STARTS THE WHOLE MARRIAGE OFF
ON THE RIGHT FOOT.

111
00:10:49,999 --> 00:10:52,001
YEAH.  YEAH.

112
00:10:54,503 --> 00:10:59,008
I KNOW WHEN YOU WERE IN THE WAR
YOU MUST HAVE HAD EXPERIENCES.

113
00:11:01,510 --> 00:11:05,514
WELL--
NO, DON'T TELL ME
ABOUT THEM !  IT WAS WARTIME.

114
00:11:05,514 --> 00:11:10,019
ANYWAY, IT'S DIFFERENT
FOR A MAN THAN FOR A WOMAN.
I UNDERSTAND.

115
00:11:10,019 --> 00:11:12,021
JUST SO GLAD WE WAITED.

116
00:11:12,021 --> 00:11:14,023
SO AM I.

117
00:11:18,027 --> 00:11:23,532
AND YOU KNOW WHAT ?
I'M GONNA LOSE WEIGHT
JUST FOR YOU, BILLY.

118
00:11:23,532 --> 00:11:27,036
SEE.
BEFORE I NEEDED A REASON,

119
00:11:27,036 --> 00:11:30,539
AND NOW...
I HAVE ONE !

120
00:11:32,541 --> 00:11:38,547
HEY, BILLY.  I THINK
WE'VE BEGUN THE LIFE
OF A NEW HERO.

121
00:11:41,550 --> 00:11:46,055
HOW CAN YOU TELL ?
BECAUSE I'M A WOMAN.
[ Laughs ]

122
00:11:46,055 --> 00:11:48,557
HUH !

123
00:11:50,059 --> 00:11:54,563
AND YOU KNOW WHAT,
BILLY ?
WHAT ?

124
00:11:57,066 --> 00:12:01,070
I NEVER THOUGHT
ANYBODY WOULD EVER MARRY ME.

125
00:12:02,571 --> 00:12:04,573
I DID.

126
00:12:18,087 --> 00:12:22,091
[ Speaking German ]

127
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:34,103
[ Woman Yelling In German ]

128
00:12:44,113 --> 00:12:47,616
[ Man Speaking German ]

129
00:12:47,616 --> 00:12:49,618
[ Speaking German ]

130
00:13:01,130 --> 00:13:03,632
OH, JESUS !
STAY OFF MY FEET, WILL YA ?

131
00:13:04,133 --> 00:13:06,135
[ Laughing ]

132
00:13:18,647 --> 00:13:21,150
[ Girls Laughing, Chattering ]

133
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:25,154
[ Man ]
OH, WALK RIGHT, WILL YA ?
GEE, I'M SORRY.

134
00:13:25,154 --> 00:13:30,159
YOU STEP ON HIS FEET AGAIN,
YOU SON OF A BITCH,
AND I'LL BREAK YOUR ASS !

135
00:13:30,159 --> 00:13:32,661
YOU HEAR ME ?

136
00:13:33,162 --> 00:13:35,664
DIE BLONDE HAAR.
BRINGEN SIE MARINE.

137
00:13:35,664 --> 00:13:38,667
OVER HERE.
SCHNELL !

138
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:41,670
[ Speaking German ]

139
00:13:43,172 --> 00:13:46,175
[ Shouting In German ]

140
00:13:49,678 --> 00:13:51,680
[ Shouting
  In German ]

141
00:14:00,639 --> 00:14:05,144
[ Speaking German ]

142
00:14:05,144 --> 00:14:08,430
GOOD.  HOLD IT.
LOOK OUT HERE NOW.
CAN YOU GET THE SIGN IN ?

143
00:14:08,831 --> 00:14:11,233
THE SIGN'S
IN GOOD.
OKAY, SMILE.

144
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:14,203
LOOKS GOOD.
HOLD IT.

145
00:14:14,203 --> 00:14:16,205
BIG SMILE NOW.
 BIG SMILE !

146
00:14:16,205 --> 00:14:20,209
JA !  LACHELN.
LACHELN.  LACHELN.  JA.

147
00:14:20,709 --> 00:14:24,713
HEY, THAT'S GOOD.
HOLD THAT KISS.

148
00:14:24,713 --> 00:14:28,801
- WE GOT IT !
-[ Speaking German ]

149
00:14:28,801 --> 00:14:32,304
[ German Continues ]

150
00:14:35,808 --> 00:14:39,311
ALL YOU DOG FACES
FROM THE 451st OVER HERE.

151
00:14:39,311 --> 00:14:43,315
FALL IN HERE.
IT'S YOUR OLD COLONEL, BOYS.
IT'S WILD BOB.

152
00:14:44,316 --> 00:14:46,819
FOUR-FIFTY-FIRST.

153
00:14:46,819 --> 00:14:48,821
YOU FROM THE 451st ?

154
00:14:48,821 --> 00:14:51,824
SOME OF YOU BOYS
MUST BE FROM THE 451st.

155
00:14:51,824 --> 00:14:54,326
I KNOW YOU, DON'T I ? 
WHAT'S YOUR NAME ?

156
00:14:54,326 --> 00:14:57,329
PILGRIM, SIR.
PILGRIM.  OF COURSE !
I REMEMBER YOU.

157
00:14:57,329 --> 00:14:59,832
DAMN FINE RIFLEMAN.
FINE RIFLEMAN, PILGRIM.

158
00:14:59,832 --> 00:15:02,334
ONE OF THE BEST
IN THE 451st.

159
00:15:02,334 --> 00:15:05,337
FIRST IN PEACE,
 FIRST IN WAR, AND FIRST--

160
00:15:05,337 --> 00:15:07,339
[ Speaking German ]

161
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,342
GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME !
AN OFFICER'S PLACE
IS WITH HIS MEN !

162
00:15:10,843 --> 00:15:14,847
MY MEN NEED ME, AND I'M
STAYIN' WITH 'EM !  DON'T
WORRY; IT'S YOUR OLD COLONEL.

163
00:15:14,847 --> 00:15:17,850
WILD BOB IS WITH YOU.
NO FORMALITIES.  AT EASE.

164
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:21,353
BY GOD, WILD BOB'S
PROUD OF YOU.

165
00:15:21,353 --> 00:15:24,356
THERE ARE DEAD GERMANS
ALL OVER THE PLACE
WISHIN' TO GOD THEY'D NEVER--

166
00:15:24,356 --> 00:15:26,358
[ Coughs ]

167
00:15:28,861 --> 00:15:33,365
[ Speaking German ]
I'M STAYIN' WITH MY MEN.

168
00:15:33,365 --> 00:15:36,368
[ Speaking German ]
ALL RIGHT.  ALL RIGHT.
GOD BLESS YOU, BOYS.

169
00:15:36,368 --> 00:15:38,871
BLESS YOU, BOYS.

170
00:15:40,372 --> 00:15:42,875
BY GOD, BOY,
YOU'RE A GOOD SOLDIER.

171
00:15:42,875 --> 00:15:44,877
YOU'LL COME
THROUGH THIS ALL RIGHT.

172
00:15:44,877 --> 00:15:48,380
AND WHEN YOU
GET TO CODY, WYOMING,
JUST ASK FOR WILD BOB.

173
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:50,883
WE'LL HAVE ONE HELL
OF A REUNION.

174
00:15:52,384 --> 00:15:57,389
GOD BLESS YOU, BOYS !
BLESS YA, BOYS !

175
00:15:57,389 --> 00:16:01,894
A FAG FROLIC IN WYOMING.
I'LL BE THERE, PILGRIM,
WAITIN' FOR YOU.

176
00:16:02,895 --> 00:16:04,897
[ Soldier On Train ]
COME ON.

177
00:16:04,897 --> 00:16:10,402
THIS AIN'T SO BAD.
I BEEN IN A LOT WORSE SPOTS
THAN THIS.

178
00:16:10,402 --> 00:16:12,905
TROY.  WINTER OF '37.

179
00:16:12,905 --> 00:16:16,408
COLD ?
I'LL TELL YOU !

180
00:16:16,408 --> 00:16:21,914
OR TAKE THE TIME WATKINS
AND ME DECKED THE YARD BULL
AT WHITE RIVER JUNCTION.

181
00:16:21,914 --> 00:16:25,417
HAD US IN THE PEN
FOR THREE WEEKS IN OUR SKIVVIES.

182
00:16:25,918 --> 00:16:29,922
WOULD HAVE HAD PNEUMONIA
IF WE HADN'T JUMPED THE PLACE.

183
00:16:29,922 --> 00:16:33,926
THEY TOOK US UP TO BURLINGTON
TO CHECK US OUT.

184
00:16:34,426 --> 00:16:36,929
LAST I HEARD, JOE
WAS SOMEWHERES ON THE ALAGASH.

185
00:16:36,929 --> 00:16:41,433
YOU TRY THAT SOMETIME, PAL.

186
00:16:41,433 --> 00:16:45,938
YOU TRY THAT SOMETIME
IN FEBRUARY IN 1934,

187
00:16:45,938 --> 00:16:47,940
THEN SEE
IF THIS IS SO BAD.

188
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:50,943
THERE ARE PLENTY
OF WORSE PLACES.

189
00:16:50,943 --> 00:16:52,945
PLENTY OF WORSE PLACES.

190
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:54,947
[ Train Engine Chugging ]

191
00:16:54,947 --> 00:16:59,835
[ Woman ]  HE WAS
AT THE TOP OF HIS CLASS
IN OPTOMETRY WHEN THIS HAPPENED.

192
00:17:00,335 --> 00:17:02,838
[ Man ]
I DON'T DOUBT IT,
MRS. PILGRIM.

193
00:17:02,838 --> 00:17:05,324
THE DOCTOR SAYS
IT'S NERVOUS EXHAUSTION.

194
00:17:05,324 --> 00:17:07,326
[ Scoffs ]
OH, I'M SURE
THAT'S ALL IT IS.

195
00:17:07,326 --> 00:17:09,328
[ Mrs. Pilgrim ]
I THINK IT'S THE WAR.

196
00:17:09,328 --> 00:17:12,331
THAT CERTAINLY COULD
HAVE A LOT TO DO WITH IT.

197
00:17:12,331 --> 00:17:14,833
BUT HE HAD
SOME AWFUL EXPERIENCES.

198
00:17:15,334 --> 00:17:17,336
HE WAS IN DRESDEN
WHEN IT WAS BOMBED.

199
00:17:17,836 --> 00:17:19,838
HIS CLOSEST FRIEND
WAS KILLED THERE.

200
00:17:19,838 --> 00:17:22,341
OH, DREADFUL.
DREADFUL.

201
00:17:22,341 --> 00:17:25,611
AND HIS FATHER PASSED ON
WHILE BILLY WAS IN TRAINING.

202
00:17:26,011 --> 00:17:30,015
BUT I KNEW GOD
WOULD SEND BILLY
HOME SAFE TO ME.

203
00:17:30,015 --> 00:17:33,018
I PRAYED EVERY NIGHT,
MR. ROSEWATER.

204
00:17:33,018 --> 00:17:35,988
EVEN THOUGH WE DON'T
BELONG TO A CHURCH.

205
00:17:35,988 --> 00:17:40,426
WE'RE ALL
IN GOD'S HANDS, DEAR.

206
00:17:44,179 --> 00:17:47,082
BILLY !
 BILLY, MAMA'S HERE.

207
00:17:47,583 --> 00:17:49,585
YOU CAN COME OUT NOW.

208
00:17:52,588 --> 00:17:54,590
HE'S ENGAGED
TO A VERY RICH GIRL.

209
00:17:54,590 --> 00:17:59,094
HER NAME'S VALENCIA.
VALENCIA MERBLE.
HER FATHER'S LIONEL MERBLE.

210
00:17:59,094 --> 00:18:03,599
HE OWNS THE
ILIUM SCHOOL OF OPTOMETRY
WHERE BILLY WAS GOING.

211
00:18:03,599 --> 00:18:08,604
HE'S BUILDING A BRAND-NEW
HOME FOR THEM ON THE LAKE
FOR A WEDDING PRESENT.

212
00:18:08,604 --> 00:18:11,106
[ Whispers ]
IT'S A SURPRISE.

213
00:18:11,106 --> 00:18:14,610
BILLY.  BILLY,
SWEETHEART.

214
00:18:14,610 --> 00:18:18,113
THE WAR IS OVER.
YOU CAN COME OUT NOW.

215
00:18:19,114 --> 00:18:22,117
PILGRIM !
YOU KILLED ME, PILGRIM.

216
00:18:23,118 --> 00:18:25,120
YOU SON OF A BITCH.

217
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:29,124
YOU CALL MY MOM AND DAD
IN PITTSBURGH, SEE.

218
00:18:29,124 --> 00:18:31,627
YOU TELL THEM I DIED
AND THAT YOU KILLED ME !

219
00:18:31,627 --> 00:18:35,130
[ Breathing Unevenly ]

220
00:18:38,133 --> 00:18:40,636
WEARY.

221
00:18:42,638 --> 00:18:44,640
THIS IS PAUL LAZZARO, WEARY.

222
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:47,142
I'LL GET REVENGE FOR YOU.

223
00:18:47,643 --> 00:18:49,645
LAZZARO.
YEAH.

224
00:18:54,650 --> 00:19:00,155
DID I EVER TELL YOU
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE DOG ?
IT'S HOT.

225
00:19:00,155 --> 00:19:03,659
SON-OF-A-BITCH DOG BIT ME.
SO I GOT SOME STEAK,

226
00:19:03,659 --> 00:19:08,163
AND I GOT THIS SPRING OUT
OF A CLOCK, AND I CUT THAT
SPRING UP INTO LITTLE PIECES.

227
00:19:08,163 --> 00:19:13,168
I STUCK IT INTO THE STEAK.
WAY INSIDE.  I WENT TO WHERE
THEY HAD THAT DOG TIED UP.

228
00:19:13,168 --> 00:19:17,172
I SAID, "HEY, BOY.
I'M NOT MAD.  COME ON.
LET'S BE FRIENDS."

229
00:19:17,172 --> 00:19:21,176
AND I THREW HIM THE STEAK,
AND I WAITED AROUND
FOR AROUND TEN MINUTES.

230
00:19:21,176 --> 00:19:26,181
AND HE STARTED CRYIN',
AND THE BLOOD SPILLED
OUT OF HIS MOUTH.

231
00:19:26,181 --> 00:19:30,185
HE TRIED TO CHEW OUT
HIS OWN INSIDES, AND I SAID,

232
00:19:30,185 --> 00:19:32,688
[ Laughing ]
"HEY, BOY.

233
00:19:32,688 --> 00:19:36,692
THAT'S ME INSIDE THERE
WITH THOSE KNIVES."

234
00:19:36,692 --> 00:19:41,196
ANYBODY ASK YOU
THE SWEETEST THING IN THE WORLD,

235
00:19:41,697 --> 00:19:43,198
IT'S REVENGE.

236
00:19:53,208 --> 00:19:55,711
WEARY'S DEAD, PILGRIM.

237
00:19:59,715 --> 00:20:02,217
[ Man ]
THE PATIENT HAS BEEN
SUFFERING FROM TRAUMA...

238
00:20:02,217 --> 00:20:05,220
WHICH CAN BE TREATED
BY ELECTRIC SHOCK.

239
00:20:05,220 --> 00:20:07,222
HELLO, BILLY.
HELLO.

240
00:20:07,222 --> 00:20:11,226
WE'VE PRESCRIBED A SERIES OF 12,
AND WE'RE UP TO NUMBER SEVEN.

241
00:20:11,226 --> 00:20:14,730
THE PATIENT WAS
A PRISONER OF WAR IN DRESDEN
WHEN IT WAS BOMBED.

242
00:20:14,730 --> 00:20:19,234
HE CLAIMS THAT WELL OVER
100,000 PEOPLE WERE BURNED
TO DEATH IN THE FIRE.

243
00:20:19,234 --> 00:20:22,237
WORSE THAN HIROSHIMA.
AND SINCE BILLY
WAS ACTUALLY THERE,

244
00:20:22,237 --> 00:20:27,743
IT'S NATURAL TO ASSUME THAT THIS
HAS HAD A CONTRIBUTING EFFECT
ON HIS PRESENT CONDITION.

245
00:20:28,243 --> 00:20:32,748
HE'S READY, DOCTOR.
YOU'RE GOING TO SLEEP NOW,
BILLY.

246
00:20:32,748 --> 00:20:36,752
[ Train Whistle Blowing ]

247
00:20:36,752 --> 00:20:40,255
[ Whistle Continues ]

248
00:21:23,298 --> 00:21:26,802
[ Brakes Screeching ]

249
00:21:43,819 --> 00:21:45,821
AUFSTIEGEN.

250
00:21:45,821 --> 00:21:47,823
WAS IS LOS ?
AROUSE !

251
00:21:48,323 --> 00:21:50,826
AROUSE !

252
00:21:54,329 --> 00:21:57,833
[ Soldiers Speaking German ]

253
00:22:02,838 --> 00:22:04,840
[ Soldier ]
 SCHNELL !

254
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:28,363
[ Shouting In German
  Continues ]

255
00:22:44,379 --> 00:22:47,382
[ Speaking German ]

256
00:22:47,382 --> 00:22:49,885
[ Speaking German ]

257
00:22:51,386 --> 00:22:53,889
[ Laughing ]
[ Soldier Laughing ]

258
00:22:56,391 --> 00:22:59,394
[ Laughing Continues ]

259
00:22:59,394 --> 00:23:01,897
[ Speaking German ]

260
00:23:25,420 --> 00:23:28,423
NAME ?
PAUL LAZZARO.

261
00:23:28,423 --> 00:23:30,425
THAT'S TWO Z'S.

262
00:23:30,425 --> 00:23:34,930
PARENTS ?
I DON'T GOT NO FAMILY.
 I SAID TWO Z'S.

263
00:23:34,930 --> 00:23:38,433
TO WHOM WE SEND THE NUMBER
IN CASE OF DEATH ?
SEND IT TO HIM.

264
00:23:42,437 --> 00:23:44,940
THIS IS YOUR TAG.
DON'T FORGET IT.

265
00:23:44,940 --> 00:23:47,943
[ Exhales ]
JA, WOHL.

266
00:23:50,445 --> 00:23:51,947
[ Soldier ]
NAME ?

267
00:23:52,447 --> 00:23:53,949
PARENTS ?

268
00:23:54,449 --> 00:23:57,953
YOU WANT IT NOW, PILGRIM ?
OR IN THE MORNING ?
WHAT DO YOU WANT ?

269
00:23:57,953 --> 00:24:00,956
- HEY, HEY !  WHY ME ?
-AUFSTEHEN !

270
00:24:00,956 --> 00:24:03,458
OH, YOU'RE
ON MY LIST, PAL.

271
00:24:03,959 --> 00:24:05,961
-AUFSTEHEN !
-AUFSTEHEN.

272
00:24:05,961 --> 00:24:07,963
[ Yelling In German ]

273
00:24:09,464 --> 00:24:13,468
GEAR IT DOWN, FELLA.
THESE GERMANS CAN BE
AWFULLY MEAN.

274
00:24:13,468 --> 00:24:15,971
OH, YEAH ?
WELL, THEY DON'T
KNOW PAUL LAZZARO.

275
00:24:16,471 --> 00:24:19,975
LISTEN.  WE AMERICANS
HAVE GOT TO STICK TOGETHER.

276
00:24:19,975 --> 00:24:22,477
WHO ARE YOU, POP ?
I'M EDGAR DERBY.

277
00:24:22,477 --> 00:24:25,981
YEAH ?  WELL,
I GOT SOMETHIN'
FOR YOU TO STICK, DERBY.

278
00:24:25,981 --> 00:24:28,984
[ Breathing Heavily ]

279
00:24:31,987 --> 00:24:35,991
[ Angrily Speaking German  ]
ALL RIGHT.  ALL RIGHT.

280
00:24:35,991 --> 00:24:39,995
HEY, YOU FUCKIN' GOON !
ALL RIGHT.
I'M TAKIN' 'EM OFF !

281
00:24:39,995 --> 00:24:43,999
LEAVE ME ALONE !
I'LL TAKE 'EM OFF !
I'M WARNIN' YA, PAL.

282
00:24:44,499 --> 00:24:46,001
[ Chattering ]

283
00:24:48,003 --> 00:24:49,938
ALL RIGHT, SON.
OVER HERE.

284
00:24:57,679 --> 00:25:02,184
HERE WE GO, BILLY BOY.
I'LL DRY YOU OFF.
TIME TO SINK OR SWIM !

285
00:25:02,184 --> 00:25:05,187
THAT'S THE WAY
TO DO IT, PILGRIM.
BEST THING FOR HIM.

286
00:25:05,187 --> 00:25:08,190
BY GOD, PILGRIM.
YOU'RE REALLY GONNA DO IT.

287
00:25:08,690 --> 00:25:13,128
YOU BET YOUR BOOTS I'M GONNA
DO IT.  HIS MAMA'S NOT GONNA
KEEP HIM ALL OF HIS LIFE.

288
00:25:13,128 --> 00:25:16,231
MY OLD MAN DID THE SAME TO ME.
DONE ME A WORLD OF GOOD.

289
00:25:16,231 --> 00:25:18,733
OH, YOU BETCHA !
IT'S THE ONLY WAY !

290
00:25:18,733 --> 00:25:22,237
WELL, THIS IS IT, BILLY BOY.
IT'S SINK OR SWIM !

291
00:25:22,237 --> 00:25:25,257
AND DON'T--
[ Men Laughing ]

292
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:31,663
[ Man ]
BILLY ?

293
00:25:31,663 --> 00:25:33,665
BILLY ?

294
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:36,801
BILLY !

295
00:26:02,827 --> 00:26:05,830
WHO ARE THEY ?
THEY'RE RUSSIAN PRISONERS.

296
00:26:15,340 --> 00:26:18,343
[ Shouting Commands
  In German ]

297
00:26:21,529 --> 00:26:24,966
?? HAIL, HAIL
  THE YANKS ARE HERE ??

298
00:26:24,966 --> 00:26:28,970
?? JOIN THE MEN FROM DOVER
  'TIL THE WAR IS OVER ??

299
00:26:28,970 --> 00:26:32,974
?
?? WE BID YOU WELCOME HERE ?

300
00:26:32,974 --> 00:26:37,479
?? WITH A LITTLE FOOD AND CHEER
  YOU'RE WELCOME HERE ??

301
00:26:37,979 --> 00:26:40,982
?? TO SHARE OUR FOOD ??

302
00:26:40,982 --> 00:26:44,486
?? AND CHEER ????

303
00:26:44,486 --> 00:26:47,489
[ Chattering ]

304
00:26:47,489 --> 00:26:49,991
EVENING.
COME ALONG INSIDE.

305
00:26:49,991 --> 00:26:51,993
WE'VE ORGANIZED
A LITTLE WELCOME.

306
00:26:51,993 --> 00:26:54,496
WE HAD A COUPLE OF DAYS NOTICE
OF YOUR ARRIVAL.

307
00:26:54,496 --> 00:26:56,498
THAT GAVE US
AN OPPORTUNITY TO PREPARE.

308
00:26:56,498 --> 00:27:00,001
HEAR YOU HAD
A PRETTY BEASTLY TIME IN BONDEM.
JERRY PUT ON QUITE A SHOW.

309
00:27:00,001 --> 00:27:02,504
IT CAN'T LAST FOREVER,
CAN IT ?

310
00:27:02,504 --> 00:27:05,507
[ Chattering ]

311
00:27:19,904 --> 00:27:23,908
- WHERE'D YOU GET ALL THIS ?
- RED CROSS.  CLERICAL ERROR.

312
00:27:23,908 --> 00:27:26,911
THEY'VE BEEN SENDING US 500
PARCELS A MONTH INSTEAD OF 50.

313
00:27:26,911 --> 00:27:29,914
THREE YEARS NOW.  WE'VE
GOT RATHER A LOT, ACTUALLY.

314
00:27:29,914 --> 00:27:31,916
SHOULDN'T YOU TELL 'EM ?

315
00:27:31,916 --> 00:27:33,918
SHOULDN'T YOU
GIVE IT BACK ?

316
00:27:33,918 --> 00:27:38,923
OH, YANK.  YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
IN THE FIGHT VERY LONG,
HAVE YOU ?

317
00:27:38,923 --> 00:27:42,927
COME ALONG.  I KEEP FORGETTING
WARS HAVE ALWAYS BEEN FOUGHT
BY CHILDREN.

318
00:27:42,927 --> 00:27:46,931
WHERE DID YOU
GET THIS ABSURD GARMENT ?
THEY GAVE IT TO ME.

319
00:27:46,931 --> 00:27:48,933
WHO ?
THE GERMANS.

320
00:27:48,933 --> 00:27:53,938
THEY DIDN'T GIVE YOU A COAT,
YANK, THEY GAVE YOU AN INSULT.
HEY, SON.  OVER HERE.

321
00:28:05,150 --> 00:28:07,152
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT I'M SAYING ?

322
00:28:07,152 --> 00:28:09,654
JERRY TRIED
TO HUMILIATE YOU.

323
00:28:09,654 --> 00:28:14,659
NOW YOU MUST WEAR THAT COAT
AS IF YOU WERE PROUD OF IT.
TEACH HIM A LESSON.

324
00:28:16,161 --> 00:28:18,663
IT'S TERRIBLY IMPORTANT
THAT YOU UNDERSTAND THAT.

325
00:28:18,663 --> 00:28:22,167
IT'S BEEN ALMOST FOUR YEARS
SINCE I WAS TAKEN PRISONER.
TRUE, MOST OF US HERE.

326
00:28:22,167 --> 00:28:26,671
WE HAVEN'T SEEN A WOMAN
OR A CHILD IN ALL OF THAT TIME.
THINK ABOUT THAT FOR A MINUTE.

327
00:28:28,673 --> 00:28:30,675
WANT TO KNOW
HOW WE SURVIVED ?

328
00:28:31,176 --> 00:28:32,677
WELL, I'LL TELL YOU.

329
00:28:33,178 --> 00:28:34,846
THE DAY THAT I WAS CAPTURED,

330
00:28:35,246 --> 00:28:37,298
I MADE A PROMISE TO MYSELF:

331
00:28:37,298 --> 00:28:39,734
EACH DAY I WOULD
BRUSH MY TEETH, SHAVE MY BEARD,

332
00:28:40,135 --> 00:28:44,956
WASH MY HANDS AND FACE
BEFORE EACH MEAL, EVACUATE
MY BOWELS WITH REGULARITY.

333
00:28:44,956 --> 00:28:47,942
AND DO YOU KNOW WHY ?

334
00:28:49,444 --> 00:28:53,948
BECAUSE THE WAR CONSISTS OF
CONTINUAL PETTY HUMILIATIONS.

335
00:28:53,948 --> 00:28:57,952
AND I FOR ONE WAS GOING
TO TREAT MYSELF WITH A GOOD DEAL
OF SELF-RESPECT AND SURVIVE.

336
00:28:57,952 --> 00:29:00,171
DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN DO IT ?

337
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:12,684
?? JOHNNY FEDORA MET
  ALICE BLUE BONNET ??

338
00:29:12,684 --> 00:29:17,906
?? IN THE WINDOW
  OF A DEPARTMENT STORE ??
GET IT !

339
00:29:17,906 --> 00:29:19,974
?? IT WAS LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT ??
COME ON !  COME ON !

340
00:29:19,974 --> 00:29:22,477
?
?? AND THEY PROMISED ONE NIGHT ?

341
00:29:22,477 --> 00:29:27,499
-?? THEY'D BE SWEETHEARTS
   FOREVERMORE ??
- BILLY.  LUNCHTIME, HON.

342
00:29:27,499 --> 00:29:31,503
?
OKAY,
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.
?? JOHNNY WOULD SERENADE ALICE ?

343
00:29:31,503 --> 00:29:35,907
?? TOO RA LEI, TOO RA LIE
   TOO RA LOO ??
SPOT, SIT.  SIT.  STAY.

344
00:29:35,907 --> 00:29:40,712
SPOT, SIT.  SIT !
?? HE SANG
  OF A BEAUTIFUL PALACE ??

345
00:29:40,712 --> 00:29:45,116
?? OF A BEAUTIFUL HATBOX
   OF BLUE ??
HEEL.  THAT'S RIGHT.

346
00:29:45,116 --> 00:29:49,521
BILLY.  BILLY.  WANT A SNACK ?
?? BUT JOHNNY FEDORA
  LOST ALICE BLUE BONNET ??

347
00:29:49,521 --> 00:29:54,726
BE RIGHT IN.
?? TO A PATRON
  OF THE DEPARTMENT STORE ??

348
00:29:55,126 --> 00:29:59,130
?? HER BEAUTY WAS SOUGHT BY
  THE GIRL SHE WAS BOUGHT BY ??
SPOT !

349
00:29:59,531 --> 00:30:03,134
?? FOR $23.94 ????

350
00:30:03,134 --> 00:30:05,136
[ Dog Barking ]

351
00:30:07,138 --> 00:30:09,140
COME ON, SPOT.
YOU CAN DO IT.

352
00:30:09,140 --> 00:30:12,343
COME ON, BOY !
 COME ON, SPOT.

353
00:30:12,343 --> 00:30:14,946
COME ON !
 COME ON, BOY !

354
00:30:14,946 --> 00:30:18,750
COME ON.  JUMP IN.
 COME ON.  JUMP !

355
00:30:18,750 --> 00:30:20,752
ATTA, BOY !

356
00:30:20,752 --> 00:30:24,756
GOOD DOG, SPOT.
[ Siren Wailing ]

357
00:30:24,756 --> 00:30:27,158
GOOD.

358
00:30:27,158 --> 00:30:29,561
BILLY !

359
00:30:31,563 --> 00:30:33,314
- BILLY !
- YEAH ?

360
00:30:33,314 --> 00:30:37,318
-SUPPER TIME, HON.
- BE RIGHT IN.

361
00:30:37,318 --> 00:30:40,522
SPOT, SIT UP.
?? HE LOOKED FOR HER UPTOWN ??
  [ Continues Indistinct ]

362
00:30:40,522 --> 00:30:43,024
[ Val ]
YOU THINK SO ?
COME ON.  LOOK AT THAT !

363
00:30:43,024 --> 00:30:48,646
NOW, ROLL OVER, SPOT.
ATTA, BOY.  ISN'T HE GREAT ?

364
00:30:48,646 --> 00:30:51,649
WHERE'S DADDY ?
THAT'S RIGHT.

365
00:30:51,649 --> 00:30:55,153
WHERE'S MOMMY ?
WHERE'S MOMMY ?
WH-WHERE'S MOMMY ?

366
00:30:55,153 --> 00:30:58,156
THAT'S RIGHT.
HI, SPOT.  SPOT !

367
00:30:58,656 --> 00:31:03,878
OH, BILLY !  GET THAT
GODDAMN MUTT OUT OF HERE.
GET HIM OUT OF HERE.  OUT !

368
00:31:03,878 --> 00:31:05,880
[ Crying ]

369
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:07,882
[ Val ]
OH, POOR BARBIE.

370
00:31:07,882 --> 00:31:11,102
THAT ANIMAL !
HE'S RUINED THREE CARPETS,
TWO PAIRS OF SHOES--

371
00:31:11,102 --> 00:31:13,104
HE'S DRIVING ME CRAZY.

372
00:31:13,104 --> 00:31:20,061
?? FOR TRUE LOVE
  WILL COME SMILING THROUGH ????

373
00:31:24,065 --> 00:31:27,569
YOU'RE OKAY, SPOT.
 YOU'RE OKAY.

374
00:31:28,570 --> 00:31:32,574
YOU MAKE A LITTLE MISTAKE
NOW AND THEN, BUT YOU'RE OKAY.

375
00:31:32,574 --> 00:31:34,576
YOU GOT HEART.

376
00:31:37,579 --> 00:31:42,083
YEAH.  OLD SPOT.

377
00:31:44,986 --> 00:31:50,992
???? [ Classical ]

378
00:33:02,030 --> 00:33:04,532
[ Lazzaro Whispering ]
PILGRIM.

379
00:33:04,532 --> 00:33:07,535
PILGRIM.

380
00:33:07,535 --> 00:33:09,537
PILGRIM !

381
00:33:09,537 --> 00:33:12,040
CAN YA HEAR ME, PILGRIM ?

382
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:14,542
HUH ?  CAN YA
HEAR ME, PILGRIM ?

383
00:33:14,542 --> 00:33:17,045
WHEN DO YOU WANT IT ?
 WHEN DO YOU WANT IT ?

384
00:33:17,545 --> 00:33:20,548
YOU'LL NEVER KNOW WHEN
IT'S GONNA HAPPEN.  MAYBE YEARS.
WHAT'S GOIN' ON ?

385
00:33:20,548 --> 00:33:23,551
-ALL RIGHT, SON.
- THIS PORK CHOP
  KILLED A FRIEND.

386
00:33:23,551 --> 00:33:25,553
- I DIDN'T.  I JUST--
- THIS MAN IS SICK.

387
00:33:25,553 --> 00:33:27,555
YEAH ?  WELL,
HE'S GONNA BE DEAD.
OUT.

388
00:33:28,056 --> 00:33:30,058
YOU WANNA MAKE THE LIST ?
OUTSIDE, LAZZARINO.

389
00:33:30,058 --> 00:33:33,061
LAZZARO !
 L-A-Z--
OUT !

390
00:33:33,061 --> 00:33:37,065
YOU THREATEN THIS MAN AGAIN,
I'LL BREAK YOU IN HALF.

391
00:33:40,568 --> 00:33:42,570
[ Clears Throat ]

392
00:33:42,570 --> 00:33:46,574
DON'T EVER ANSWER THE DOOR.
YOU TELL 'EM WHAT HAPPENS.

393
00:33:46,574 --> 00:33:50,078
NOBODY FUCKS AROUND
WITH PAUL LAZZARO.
YOU TELL 'EM !

394
00:33:51,579 --> 00:33:54,582
BOY'S ALL TWISTED UP INSIDE.

395
00:33:54,582 --> 00:33:56,584
FEELIN' BETTER ?

396
00:33:56,584 --> 00:33:58,586
YES, THANK YOU.

397
00:33:58,586 --> 00:34:03,091
WHAT'S HE GOT AGAINST YOU ?
HE'S GOT THIS CRAZY IDEA
I CAUSED HIS FRIEND'S DEATH.

398
00:34:03,591 --> 00:34:05,593
I DIDN'T, I--
I'M SURE YOU DIDN'T.

399
00:34:06,594 --> 00:34:09,097
I'LL TALK SOME TURKEY
TO THAT BOY.

400
00:34:12,100 --> 00:34:15,603
- WHAT HAPPENED ?
- YOU PASSED OUT,
  AND I BROUGHT YOU IN HERE.

401
00:34:17,605 --> 00:34:21,109
HERE.  TRY SOME OF THIS.

402
00:34:21,109 --> 00:34:23,111
THIS WILL FIX YOU UP.

403
00:34:23,111 --> 00:34:25,613
KINDA HOT.

404
00:34:26,614 --> 00:34:28,616
THANK YOU.

405
00:34:31,119 --> 00:34:35,123
- ATTA, BOY.
  TASTE PRETTY GOOD ?
- UH-HUH.

406
00:34:36,124 --> 00:34:37,625
[ Sighs ]

407
00:34:38,126 --> 00:34:43,131
YOU DON'T HAVE TO STAY.
WHAT THE HECK.
MIGHT AS WELL.

408
00:34:43,631 --> 00:34:45,133
I GOT SOME FOOD
BACK THERE.

409
00:34:45,633 --> 00:34:49,137
I DON'T MEAN TO BE IMPOLITE,
BUT HOW COME YOU'RE
IN THE ARMY ?

410
00:34:49,137 --> 00:34:53,141
I COULDN'T STAY OUT.
NOT WITH THE NAZIS
AND JAPANESE...

411
00:34:53,141 --> 00:34:55,143
THREATENING
TO CONQUER THE WORLD.

412
00:34:55,143 --> 00:34:58,646
I'VE GOT A BOY YOUR AGE
SEEING ACTION
IN THE SOUTH PACIFIC.

413
00:34:58,646 --> 00:35:01,649
HEY, THAT'S
REALLY SOMETHING.
YEAH.

414
00:35:01,649 --> 00:35:05,653
I USED TO TELL MY STUDENTS
THERE'S A MONSTER
LOOSE IN THE WORLD.

415
00:35:05,653 --> 00:35:08,656
I GOT TIRED
OF TELLING THEM,
AND I JOINED UP.

416
00:35:08,656 --> 00:35:11,159
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE A TEACHER.
OH, COME ON.

417
